System.Description.newValue:
• Alter dbo.spCustomerInfoDelete to be a standard CRUD operation and only handle the deletion of the record (the audit should be handled via the audit trigger)
  • Alter dbo.updinsCustomerInfo trigger to follow the audit trigger standard
  • Rename dbo.updinsCustomerInfo to follow the audit trigger naming convention

Microsoft.VSTS.Common.AcceptanceCriteria.newValue:
declare @id int = 123
exec dbo.spCustomerInfoDelete @pCustomerInfoID = @id, @pUserContactId = 123

Expected result:
  • The record is deleted from the dbo.CustomerInfo table.
  • Audit record is inserted into Enterprise.dbo.CustomerInfoAudit table
  • Audit record has UpdatedByContactID set to the @pUserContactId value

Regression testing:
When inserting/updating records in dbo.CustomerInfo table, corresponding audit records are inserted into Enterprise.dbo.CustomerInfoAudit table
